definition: improper/presumptuous/assuming/overstepping one's bounds/also written 非份[fei1 fen4]
abbr. for 非洲[Fei1 zhou1], Africa
to not be/not/wrong/incorrect/non-/un-/in-/to reproach or blame/(colloquial) to insist on/simply must

to divide/to separate/to distribute/to allocate/to distinguish (good and bad)/part or subdivision/fraction/one tenth (of certain units)/unit of length equivalent to 0.33 cm/minute (unit of time)/minute (angular measurement unit)/a point (in sports or games)/0.01 yuan (unit of money)

sentences.chinese: 非分阶段物质能否预注册？

sentences.english: It goes far beyond the guy who always wants to mooch lunch off of me, too.
sentences.chinese: 这样会使经常缠着我蹭饭吃的人产生非分之想。

sentences.english: Wanting more, even wanting to know more, was presumption on my part.
sentences.chinese: 想多要，甚至想多了解，在我来说都是非分之想。

sentences.english: Happy is he who only desires what he may and does what he ought.
sentences.chinese: 不作非分之想又能尽其本分的人是快乐的。

sentences.english: Non-phase-in substances are therefore normally new substances.
sentences.chinese: 非分阶段物质通常是新的物质。

sentences.english: You tried to teach me right from wrong .
sentences.chinese: 您费尽心机学人是非分明。

sentences.english: Your daughter asked no more than due.
sentences.chinese: 你女儿没有提非分要求。

sentences.english: A non-blocking matrix allows multiple paths to be connected simultaneously through the matrix.
sentences.chinese: 非分块矩阵则能够通过矩阵同时连接多条通路。

sentences.english: She had not the faintest claim to a share in Mr. Touchett's relic.
sentences.chinese: 她对杜歇先生的遗产是不能存非分之想的。

sentences.english: As an idiom, "Six Gurgoyles" means being restless due to one's immoderate ambitions.
sentences.chinese: 在成语里，“五脊六兽”形容因有非分之想而忐忑。

sentences.english: Try not to lay your hands on anything that you're not entitled to.
sentences.chinese: 不属于你的东西不要做非分之想。

sentences.english: Example : The air in the morning is quite crisp.
sentences.chinese: 早晨空气非分特别清新。

definition: improper/presumptuous/assuming/overstepping one's bounds/also written 非分[fei1 fen4]
to run off the track/to step out of line/to overstep the bounds of propriety
to overstep etiquette/not to observe priorities
avaricious and insatiable (idiom); greedy and never satisfied
(of greed, lust etc) to dominate one's thoughts
